Most of the Milky Way's mass is locked up in dark matter.

The lensing galaxy, however, is underweight in terms of its dark-matter content.

'The unusually small amount of dark matter in this massive, elliptical, lensing galaxy is very surprising,' Suyu said.

'Other elliptical galaxies that are closer to us have much more dark matter and have inventories of stars that appear to be different from this super-distant lensing galaxy.'

The team's results appeared in the July 10 issue of The Astrophysical Journal Letters.

